This solution may be interpreted as the pressure drop at a distance r  because of a volume of
fluid,  q˜,  instantaneously  withdrawn  at  r  =  0  and  t  =  0.  Consistent  with  this  interpretation,
q˜/ (Φc)is the strength of the source, which is the pressure drop in a unit volume of the porous
medium caused by the instantaneous withdrawal of a volume of fluid, q˜ (see Eq. 3.155).

Instantaneous Point Source in an Infinite Reservoir.  Nisle21 presented a more general solu-
tion  for  an  instantaneous  point  source  of  strength  q˜/ (Φc)  acting  at  t  =  τ  in  an  infinite,
homogeneous, but anisotropic reservoir as

Δp(M, M′, t − τ) =

q˜

